pacity, interactional learning, and instructed learning via a variety of conceptual frameworks and methodological strategies. These studies, as well as the suggestions for future research, will be of great interest to second language acquisition researchers, graduate students and second language teachers of Chinese, as well as to curriculum developers and materials writers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChinese languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aacquisition of Chinese as a foreign language.  aacquisition of Chinese as a second language.  aacquisition of Chinese as an L2.  alearning Chinese as a second language.  alearning Chinese as an L2.  alearning Chinese.1 aHan, ZhaoHon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHan, ZhaoHong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHan, ZhaoHong, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJin, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Shaofeng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaeng, Joo-oeck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWen, Xiaohong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWu, Shu-Ling, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWu, Yongan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G